<script>
    const teaCup = document.getElementById("teaCup");
    const speechBubble = document.getElementById("speechBubble");
    const teaCups = [
        "/icons/tea.png",
        "/icons/tea_2.png",
        "/icons/tea_3.png",
        "/icons/tea_4.png",
    ];
    let currentCup = 0;

    teaCup.addEventListener("click", () => {
        // Change tea cup
        currentCup = (currentCup + 1) % teaCups.length;
        teaCup.src = teaCups[currentCup];

        // Wiggle animation
        teaCup.classList.add("wiggle");
        setTimeout(() => teaCup.classList.remove("wiggle"), 500);

        // Show speech bubble
        speechBubble.classList.add("show");
        setTimeout(() => speechBubble.classList.remove("show"), 2000);
    });
</script>

        <main tabindex="-1" id="main-content">
            
<article><h2>current goals</h2>
<ul>
<li>Four large greenhouses on the expanded part of my farm (tea, wheat, rice, sugar cane)
<ul>
<li>It might make sense to start with four <em>small</em> greenhouses because the large ones are so expensive</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Larger orchard area to the left of my house
<ul>
<li>Row of each type of tree</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Small barn just for horses + large coop for rabbits &amp; capybaras
<ul>
<li>Doesn’t make sense to do this until I’ve finished unlocking all the skills from the Caldarus statue, because I would <em>really</em> need a steady supply of essence stones to keep up with caring for all the livestock</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>+1 house upgrade</li>
<li>Decorate the area in front of the Caldarus statue</li>
</ul>
<h2>essence stones</h2>
<p>My eventual goal is to have essence stones powering my entire farm so I can spend all my time foraging, mining, and fishing. I know this will take a lot of essence stones, though — and I haven’t finished unlocking all my skills yet, so right now, I’m just using essence stones in each barn/coop so I don’t have to manually pet my livestock every day.</p>
<p>I’m thinking I’d need about:</p>
<ul>
<li>4 for greenhouses</li>
<li>6 for seasonal crops</li>
<li>5 for coops &amp; barns</li>
<li>5 for crops to feed livestock</li>
<li><strong>20 total</strong> essence stones</li>
</ul>
<p>If I want to use giant essence stones, which last for 40 days, I’d need 1600 total stones and 4000 essence. Which is a crazy amount, but I’d have 40 whole days to get it for each cycle.</p>
<p>Need to figure out how much stone + essence I tend to get on average when I spend a day mining to give me an idea of how many days I’d have to spend mining to maintain this. If it’s unrealistic, I could maybe just not use essence stones for seasonal crops.</p>
</article>

